    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Emergency Exit Latches and Alarms</title>
        <para>The bus is equipped with an emergency door latch and driver warning switch that is activated when the door
            latch mechanism (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700372">Figure 72, Item 1</hotlnk>) is opened. This switch activates (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700372">Figure 72, Item 4</hotlnk>) an alarm and flashing light at the driver's control
            panel.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700372" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g4700372.webp" filename="../figg47/G4700372.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 72. Emergency Exit Door and Related Hardware</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY DOOR LATCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">CUSHIONED HEAD BUMPER</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">REAR WINDOW ASSEMBLY- DRIVER SIDE</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY DOOR LATCH RELAY ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">BOLT LATCH (OPTIONAL WITH STARTER INTERLOCKS)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY EXIT DOOR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para></para>
        <para></para>
        <para></para>
