        <para></para>
        <para></para>
        <para></para>
        <para>The emergency roof escape hatch (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700373">Figure 73, Item 2</hotlnk>) when specified allows egress from the interior of the
            bus in situations when the bus may not be in an upright position. The roof escape hatch when specified is
            available with a lift up vent opening (
            <hotlnk document="s47003_6.xml" xrefid="f4700325">Figure 25, Item 1</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700373" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g4700373.webp" filename="../figg47/G4700373.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="280px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 73. Emergency Roof Exit Hatch</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">ROOF MOUNTED FRAME AND MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY ROOF HATCH</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">EMERGENCY EXIT HATCH RELEASE HANDLE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
